LISBON, Jan. 2—Public demonstrations outside prisons were banned today in the northern city of Oporto after incidents last night during which three persons were shot dead and four gravely wounded by guards.

The New Year's Day demonstration in front of Custoias Prison in Oporto was part of a growing campaign by leftist, lorganizations to obtain the release of 140 military and civilian prisoners arrested in connection with the leftist uprising Nov. 25.

One of the victims was identified as a 22‐year‐old German student, Gtinter Bruns, from Hamburg. The official communique said that he had been “interfering in Portuguese politics” and had links with various organizations.

The other two dead were identified as Portuguese workers: 30‐year‐old Armenia Pereira da Silva and Celestino Rebelo Teixeira, 43.